responsibilities:
- As the strategic operations manager for TikTok LIVE, USDS team, you will play a critical role in helping drive the growth and success of our team;
- Set a long-term vision for team ownership, build roadmaps and development plans. Navigate technical and compliance details with cross functional teams while effectively conveying goals and prioritization - proficient in addressing both the 10-feet and 10K-feet level details;
- Lead and organize team OKRs, monitor and track performance across multiple operation verticals, identify areas for improvement and drive continuous improvement initiatives;
- Partners with senior leadership and leverage data to inform and influence new strategies, SOPs and/or collaboration models that bring business impact and improve efficiencies;
- Build relationships and ensure tight alignment with cross-functional stakeholders (e.g., Product, Regional Ops, Analytics, Legal, Compliance, etc) to drive execution excellence and align resources to deliver best output;
- Deeply understand TikTok USDS Privacy, Safety, and Security guidelines, as well as business partners' priorities across TikTok LIVE team, be the bridge and advocate to build the compliant and efficient TikTok LIVE business;
- Coaching and developing team members.

qualifications.required:
- Bachelor's degree; MBA or Master's degree preferred;
- 5+ years of experience working in product operations, user growth, and/or technology companies' strategy/business ops roles; 
- 3+ years of experience directly managing teams;
-Intermediate to advanced Excel skills;
- Analytical mindset and skills for decision making, experiences in goal setting, results-driven performance management, and/or growth strategies;
- Deep understanding of social media platforms, user lifecycle and marketplace dynamics;
- Ability to work independently and time manage multiple high impact initiatives; Proactively identifying opportunities to optimize products and processes

qualifications.preferred:
- An in-depth understanding of content business and its related technologies;
- Excellent communication and presentation skills with the ability to take complex, ambiguous topics and turn them into digestable and insightful narratives for audiences;
- Speed, resourcefulness, and a go-getter attitude;
